Command Line Lesson plan:

Commands Reference: https://www.git-tower.com/blog/posts/command-line-cheat-sheet

1. navigate directories
pwd
cd
ls

2. Clone GitHub Account
git clone url

3. Exercise: Navigate through directories

4. Create Files and Directories
touch
mkdir

5. Remove Files/Directories
rm

6. Copy/Move files
cp
mv

7. Observe Files
head
tail
cat
less

8. Find Files
find

9. Grep Files
grep

10. Permissions
chmod
-https://help.ubuntu.com/community/FilePermissions
-chmod permission number explanations: https://www.linux.org/threads/file-permissions-chmod.4124/

11. Pipes
|

-----------------------------------------
TEXT EDITOR: vim
(http://www.openvim.com/)

1. Open Text Editor
vim

2. Insert mode to add new text
i

3. Exit vim
press Esc
press Shift+:
:q!  -to quit without saving
:wq  -to quit and save
